250 g Chorizo Sausage, uncased
2 unit(s) Flatbread
1 unit(s) Gala Apple
1 unit(s) Yellow Onion
56 g Spring Mix
1 unit(s) Green Onion
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
½ cup Marinara Sauce
4 tbsp BBQ Sauce
1 tbsp White Wine Vinegar
0.13 tsp Pepper*
¼ tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
2 tbsp Oil*

Core, then cut apple into 1/4-inch slices.
Thinly slice green onion.
Peel, then cut onion into 1/2-inch slices.
Add vinegar, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk until sugar dissolves.
Add apples to dressing, then toss to combine. Set aside.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then chorizo. Cook, breaking up chorizo into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Carefully drain and discard excess fat.
Add half the BBQ sauce to chorizo. Cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, 30 sec. Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Transfer chorizo to a plate, then cover to keep warm.
Carefully wipe the pan clean.

Reheat the same pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then onions. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 3-4 min. Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Transfer onions to the plate with chorizo, then cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, arrange flatbreads on a parchment-lined baking sheet. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, use 2 parchment-lined baking sheets.)
Toast flatbreads in the middle of the oven until softened, 2-3 min. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, toast in the top and middle of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Spread marinara sauce over toasted flatbreads.
Top with chorizo and onions, then sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in the middle of the oven until cheese is melted and flatbreads are golden-brown and crisp, 6-8 min. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, bake flatbreads in the top and middle of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Add spring mix to the bowl with marinated apples. Toss to combine.
Cut flatbread pizzas into slices, then drizzle remaining BBQ sauce over top.
Sprinkle green onions over pizzas.
Divide pizzas and salad between plates.

If you've opted to get chorizo, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the beef.